                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240916-255-victim2126 t18240916-255-viclabel1366"></join>. The prisoner has been in my employ from a child. In the course of the last three or four weeks my counting-house was entered by a key, and on Sunday night last I deposited 10 s. there, in a particular situation, having previously marked them; they were put into a desk, which was not locked.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-255-person2128">
                  GEORGE 
                  GOULD
               <interp inst="t18240916-255-person2128" type="surname" value="GOULD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-255-person2128" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-255-person2128" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the son of the prosecutor. I sat up to watch the counting-house in an adjoining room, and about six o'clock on Monday morning I heard somebody walking to the door, which was opened with a key. I looked through the key-hole, and saw the prisoner go into the counting-house; he remained there five minutes, and when he came out I stopped him, and found 10 s. on him, which I gave to the constable the same morning. He had had a good character previous to this.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-255-person2129">
